ABM conditions to match

This presents the conditions that have to be matched for the inheritance of traits variance (range) during speciation. Lets call \(V_a\) the variance of the ancestor at \(t = T_s\) and \(V_1, V_2\) the variance of its descendants at \(t = T_s\).

First, each variance has to be strictly positive:

condition 1: \(V_a > 0\), \(V_1 > 0\) and \(V_2 > 0\)

Second, the ancestral variance has to be conserved:

condition 2: \(V_a â¤ V_1 + V_2 â¤ 2V_a\)

Ideally, we should allow the parametrization to meet a simple Brownian motion such as:

\(V_a = V_1 = V_2\)

Latest try

We consider a parameter controling the bigger amount of variance inherited by one the descendants:

\(\rho = \frac{V_2}{V_a}\) with \(0 < \rho â¤ 1\) and \(V_1 â¤ V_2\).

We consider another parameter controling the difference between the amount of inherited variance by descendants:

\(\delta = \frac{V_1}{V_2}\) with \(0 < \delta â¤ 1\).

With that parametrization only condition 1 is met. We have a simple BM (\(V_a = V_1 = V_2\)) with \(\rho = 1\) and \(\delta = 1\)

example with \(V_a = 5\)
